# HTTPS reverse proxy for prog-strength services.
#
# Caddy obtains a Let's Encrypt cert for each vhost on first request, auto-
# renews it, and redirects HTTP -> HTTPS. The upstream services (`api`,
# `mcp`) are only reachable on the shared docker network `prog-strength`
# — Caddy is the only container with public ports.
#
# Adding the apex (progstrength.fitness) here later, once the frontend
# lands on EC2, is a one-block addition. If the frontend goes on Vercel
# or similar, point the apex DNS record there instead and leave this file
# alone.
#
# Internal-only paths are blocked uniformly on every vhost via the
# (block_internal) snippet below. The data path is:
#
#   - /internal/*  — written to by the FastAPI agent over the in-docker
#                    network; never reachable by browsers/curl.
#   - /metrics     — scraped by Prometheus over the in-docker network;
#                    not for public exposure.
#
# Caddy responds 404 on those paths so they look like routes that
# simply don't exist on the public surface, rather than 403'ing and
# advertising that something is there to find.

(block_internal) {
	@internal path /internal/* /metrics
	respond @internal 404
}

api.progstrength.fitness {
	import block_internal
	reverse_proxy api:8080
}

mcp.progstrength.fitness {
	import block_internal
	reverse_proxy mcp:8000
}

agent.progstrength.fitness {
	import block_internal
	reverse_proxy agent:8001
}
